                      "
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 6,
      "FacilityID": 23550,
      "SummaryText": "                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            3. The worst-case release scenario(s) and the alternative release scenario(s), including administrative controls and"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 7,
      "FacilityID": 23550,
      "SummaryText": " mitigation measures to limit the distances for each reported scenario.\n\nWorst-Case Scenario. - Failure of the bulk storage tank when filled to capacity would release 81,440 pounds of toluene diisocyanate. The full capacity of this tank is 81,440 pounds at a storage temperature of 75 F. It is assumed that the entire contents are released as a liquid and vapor over a 10-minute period. \nThe distance to the endpoint of the worst-case scenario is 0.60 miles. \n                                                                                                                                                                 Alternative Scenario. - A transfer hose failure of a 15 foot length of 2 inch hose. The emergency stop valve does not function properly . The contents of the tank truck are released. The resulting unconfined  vapor may travel  beyond the plant boundary. The liquid is contained in the unloading area spill basin.\nThe distance to the endpoint for the alternative scenario is less than 0.10 mile.  \n\n4. The general accidental release prevention program and the specific prevention steps. \n\nThis production facility complies with EPA's Accidental Release Prevention Rule, OSHA's Process Safety Management of Highly Hazardous Chemicals Standard  (PSM) and with all applicable state codes and City of Elgin, Illinois regulations. This facility was designed and constructed in accordance with NFPA-30, the 1999 National Electric Code and the ANSI Code for Pressure Piping, ANSI B31.3-1993 or ANSI B31.1.  All of our employees have been trained under HAZWOPER and given safe handling and unloading procedure training for  (TDI).\n\n5. Five-year accident history. \n\nThere have been no reportable accidents at this facility in the last five years. This is a new facility.\n\n6. The emergency response program.\n\nThis facility's emergency response program incorporates the hazards of (TDI) and reflects the emergency response requirements associated with the use of (TDI). The supplier and the "
    },
